summary: TL* THE CONTACT OWNS A 2005 TOYOTA TUNDRA. WHILE THE VEHICLE WAS STATIONARY, THE CONTACT NOTICED SEVERE CORROSION ON THE REAR FRAME OF THE VEHICLE. UPON INSPECTION, IT WAS DIAGNOSED THAT THE FRAME WAS "FLAKING AWAY" DUE TO SEVERE CORROSION. THE VEHICLE WAS REPAIRED. THE MANUFACTURER WAS MADE AWARE OF THE ISSUE. THE FAILURE MILEAGE WAS 129,000.
